info.description:
jindo
====

.. contents::

Installation
------------

You can install jindo with ``easy_install jindo`` (sudo required in most cases)

You'll need to create this file and put your (mt) API key in it:

~/.jindorc

Contents:

api_key=YOUR_API_KEY


Summary
-------

Usage Examples::

    $ jindo -d -s NNNNN
         List details for service number NNNNNN



Changes
-------
**0.0.1**: Fix for yadda
           
           Add blabla


Requirements
------------

* setuptools
